==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anthocarpous
<hw>An`tho*car"pous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a`nqos</grk> flower + <grk>karpo`s</grk> fruit.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having some portion of the floral envelopes
attached to the pericarp to form the fruit, as in the checkerberry, the
mulberry, and the pineapple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anthocyanin</ent>⟦br⟧
